Note:
==============================================================================
FALCON-ZINT : multi-precision signed integers (sign-magnitude, 31-bit limbs)
==============================================================================

Storage convention. A zint is a contiguous arena-allocated block:

    offset  0  (int32)  sign        0 = nonnegative, 1 = negative
    offset  4  (int32)  used        number of "live" limbs (0 if value == 0)
    offset  8  (int32)  capacity    number of allocated limbs
    offset 12  (int32)  padding     reserved (alignment)
    offset 16  (int32[]) limbs      little-endian limbs in [0, 2^31)

Each limb stores 31 significant bits. The 32nd bit (sign bit of the
underlying int32) is reserved as a carry workspace for addition and
shifting, so we never need a temporary widening cast.

Two-stage representation. The arithmetic primitives keep the magnitude
canonical: trailing zero limbs are trimmed via zint_normalize so that
used == 0 iff the value is zero, and the top live limb is nonzero
otherwise. Sign is held as a single bit; the canonical encoding of zero
forces sign = 0.

This mirrors Pornin's zint design in falcon/zint*.c (NIST PQC Round 3
submission package) at the algorithmic level. We diverge from the
reference in two engineering ways:

  1. We use 31-bit limbs in int32 cells rather than 30-bit limbs in
     int32 cells; the spare bit is enough for additive carry only and we
     handle multiplicative carry via explicit splitting into two limbs.

  2. We store sign and length in a 16-byte header in front of the limb
     array rather than packing them into a separate descriptor, so a
     single arena_allocate returns a self-contained zint pointer.

The Falcon NTRUSolve descent peaks at roughly 2560-bit coefficients
(depth 9 of the Falcon-1024 tower); 84 limbs at 31 bits per limb covers
the worst case with margin.

Security_Scope (module-wide):
  Coefficient values are SECRET Falcon key material. The schoolbook
  multiply, Karatsuba, and the binary-extended-gcd primitives all run
  in time linear in the limb count (no early-exit on limb value), so
  the wall-clock cost depends on size but not on data. Sign bits are
  manipulated by branchless XOR / mask patterns.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena

Note:
==============================================================================
LAYOUT HELPERS
==============================================================================
:End Note

Process called "zint_header_bytes" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Return the size (in bytes) of the zint header. Used by every
    primitive that walks the limb array.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Header = 4 (sign) + 4 (used) + 4 (capacity) + 4 (padding) = 16 bytes.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return 16
End Process

Process called "zint_limb_bits" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Return the number of significant bits per limb.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Constant 31; chosen so that two 31-bit limbs fit in a 63-bit
    multiply accumulator without overflow.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return 31
End Process

Process called "zint_limb_mask" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Return the mask that isolates the low 31 bits of an int64 / int32.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    2^31 - 1 = 2147483647.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return 2147483647
End Process

Process called "zint_limb_radix" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Return the limb radix B = 2^31.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Constant 2147483648.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return 2147483648
End Process

Process called "zint_get_sign" takes z as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read the sign field of a zint.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load int32 at offset 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public layout.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return Memory.memory_get_int32(z, 0)
End Process

Process called "zint_set_sign" takes z as Integer, sign as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Write the sign field of a zint.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Store int32 at offset 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public layout.
    @End Security_Scope
    Memory.memory_set_int32(z, 0, sign)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zint_get_used" takes z as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read the used-limb count of a zint.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load int32 at offset 4.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public layout.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return Memory.memory_get_int32(z, 4)
End Process

Process called "zint_set_used" takes z as Integer, used as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Write the used-limb count of a zint.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Store int32 at offset 4.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public layout.
    @End Security_Scope
    Memory.memory_set_int32(z, 4, used)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zint_get_capacity" takes z as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read the capacity field of a zint.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load int32 at offset 8.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public layout.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return Memory.memory_get_int32(z, 8)
End Process

Process called "zint_set_capacity" takes z as Integer, cap as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Write the capacity field of a zint.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Store int32 at offset 8.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public layout.
    @End Security_Scope
    Memory.memory_set_int32(z, 8, cap)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zint_limb_addr" takes z as Integer, idx as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compute the byte address of limb idx within zint z.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    base + header_bytes + 4 * idx.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two adds and one shift.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public layout.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let hdr be proc zint_header_bytes
    Let off be hdr plus (idx multiplied by 4)
    Return z plus off
End Process

Process called "zint_get_limb" takes z as Integer, idx as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Read limb idx of zint z. Returns 0 for out-of-range indices to
    let callers walk past the used count without bounds checks.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    If idx >= used, return 0. Otherwise load the int32 at the limb's
    byte address.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single load (or zero on out-of-range).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public layout. Limb values are SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let used be proc zint_get_used with z
    If idx is greater than or equal to used:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let addr be proc zint_limb_addr with z, idx
    Return Memory.memory_get_int32(addr, 0)
End Process

Process called "zint_set_limb" takes z as Integer, idx as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Write limb idx of zint z. Caller is responsible for keeping idx
    within capacity and for masking value to 31 bits.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Store int32 at the computed limb address.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public layout. Limb values are SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let addr be proc zint_limb_addr with z, idx
    Memory.memory_set_int32(addr, 0, value)
    Return 1
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
ALLOCATION / DESTRUCTION
==============================================================================
:End Note

Process called "zint_create" takes arena as Integer, capacity as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocate a zint with capacity for `capacity` 31-bit limbs.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Allocate header + 4 * max(capacity, 1) bytes from the arena, zero
    the entire block (so sign = 0, used = 0, all limbs = 0), then
    write the capacity field.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One arena_allocate plus one memory_zero.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET zints live in the same arena as the surrounding NTRUSolve
    descent; the arena is overwritten at the end of keygen.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let safe_cap be capacity
    If safe_cap is less than 1:
        Set safe_cap to 1
    End If
    Let hdr be proc zint_header_bytes
    Let bytes be hdr plus (safe_cap multiplied by 4)
    Let z be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, bytes)
    If z is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_zero(z, bytes)
    proc zint_set_capacity with z, safe_cap
    Return z
End Process

Process called "zint_destroy" takes z as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Logically destroy a zint by zeroing its contents.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    No-op for the underlying memory (the arena owns the storage and
    will free it wholesale), but we zero the live bytes to scrub any
    SECRET material in case the caller maps the arena page somewhere
    visible.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Linear in capacity.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Helpful for SECRET hygiene; not load-bearing for correctness.
    @End Security_Scope
    If z is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cap be proc zint_get_capacity with z
    Let hdr be proc zint_header_bytes
    Let bytes be hdr plus (cap multiplied by 4)
    Memory.memory_zero(z, bytes)
    Return 1
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
NORMALIZATION
==============================================================================
:End Note

Process called "zint_normalize" takes z as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Trim trailing zero limbs and canonicalise the sign of zero so that
    every zint of the same value has the same byte representation.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Walk used downward while the top limb is zero; if used reaches 0,
    also force sign = 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(used). Branch on limb value is timing-visible only via the loop
    iteration count, which depends on the magnitude (a Falcon-permitted
    leakage path).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Operates on SECRET limbs.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let used be proc zint_get_used with z
    Let scanning be 1
    While scanning is equal to 1:
        If used is equal to 0:
            Set scanning to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let top be proc zint_get_limb with z, used minus 1
            If top is equal to 0:
                Set used to used minus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set scanning to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    proc zint_set_used with z, used
    If used is equal to 0:
        proc zint_set_sign with z, 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
ZERO / ONE / FROM_INT / TO_INT
==============================================================================
:End Note

Process called "zint_set_zero" takes z as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Force z to the canonical encoding of zero.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    sign = 0, used = 0. Limb memory is left alone; readers ignore
    limbs beyond used.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    proc zint_set_sign with z, 0
    proc zint_set_used with z, 0
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zint_is_zero" takes z as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test whether z is the canonical zero.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Returns 1 iff used == 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single load and compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let used be proc zint_get_used with z
    If used is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "zint_from_int" takes arena as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Build a zint from a signed Integer (Int64 on this target).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Split |value| into low and high 31-bit limbs. Allocate capacity 3
    (covers any Int64 magnitude up to 2^93 - 1 with margin) and store
    the limbs little-endian.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET if value carries key material.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let z be proc zint_create with arena, 3
    If z is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return z
    End If
    Let sign be 0
    Let mag be value
    If mag is less than 0:
        Set sign to 1
        Set mag to 0 minus mag
    End If
    Let mask be proc zint_limb_mask
    Let bits be proc zint_limb_bits
    Let limb0 be mag bitwise_and mask
    Let limb1 be (mag shifted right by bits) bitwise_and mask
    Let limb2 be (mag shifted right by (bits multiplied by 2)) bitwise_and mask
    proc zint_set_limb with z, 0, limb0
    proc zint_set_limb with z, 1, limb1
    proc zint_set_limb with z, 2, limb2
    proc zint_set_sign with z, sign
    proc zint_set_used with z, 3
    proc zint_normalize with z
    Return z
End Process

Process called "zint_to_int" takes z as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Convert z back to a signed Integer. Returns the value modulo 2^63
    after sign application; callers that need overflow detection should
    use zint_bit_length first.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Accumulate limbs lowest-first, shifting by 31 each step. Apply sign.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(used).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let used be proc zint_get_used with z
    Let bits be proc zint_limb_bits
    Let acc be 0
    Let i be used
    While i is greater than 0:
        Set i to i minus 1
        Let limb be proc zint_get_limb with z, i
        Set acc to (acc shifted left by bits) bitwise_or limb
    End While
    Let sign be proc zint_get_sign with z
    If sign is equal to 1:
        Set acc to 0 minus acc
    End If
    Return acc
End Process

Process called "zint_bit_length" takes z as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Return the number of significant bits in |z|. Zero returns 0.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    bits = 31 * (used - 1) + (bit position of top non-zero bit + 1).
    Find the topmost set bit of the top limb by linear scan; the limb
    has at most 31 bits so the scan is bounded.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(used + 31).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let used be proc zint_get_used with z
    If used is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let bits_per be proc zint_limb_bits
    Let top be proc zint_get_limb with z, used minus 1
    Let top_bits be 0
    While top is not equal to 0:
        Set top to top shifted right by 1
        Set top_bits to top_bits plus 1
    End While
    Let total be ((used minus 1) multiplied by bits_per) plus top_bits
    Return total
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
COPY / NEG / ABS / COMPARE
==============================================================================
:End Note

Process called "zint_copy" takes arena as Integer, src as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Duplicate a zint into a freshly allocated buffer.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Allocate capacity = src.capacity, memory_copy header+limbs.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(capacity).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let cap be proc zint_get_capacity with src
    Let dst be proc zint_create with arena, cap
    If dst is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let hdr be proc zint_header_bytes
    Let bytes be hdr plus (cap multiplied by 4)
    Memory.memory_copy(dst, src, bytes)
    Return dst
End Process

Process called "zint_copy_into" takes dst as Integer, src as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Copy src into a pre-allocated dst whose capacity must be at least
    src.used. Preserves dst.capacity.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Read src sign and used, copy used limbs, write dst sign and used,
    zero any trailing limbs of dst within its capacity.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(src.used + dst.capacity).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let used be proc zint_get_used with src
    Let sign be proc zint_get_sign with src
    Let dst_cap be proc zint_get_capacity with dst
    If used is greater than dst_cap:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than used:
        Let v be proc zint_get_limb with src, i
        proc zint_set_limb with dst, i, v
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    While i is less than dst_cap:
        proc zint_set_limb with dst, i, 0
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc zint_set_used with dst, used
    proc zint_set_sign with dst, sign
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zint_neg" takes z as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Flip the sign of z in place. Zero stays zero.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    If used == 0 keep sign 0; else XOR sign with 1.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET; CT.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let used be proc zint_get_used with z
    If used is equal to 0:
        proc zint_set_sign with z, 0
        Return 1
    End If
    Let s be proc zint_get_sign with z
    Let flipped be s bitwise_xor 1
    proc zint_set_sign with z, flipped
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zint_abs" takes z as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Force z to be nonnegative in place.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Set sign to 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET; CT.
    @End Security_Scope
    proc zint_set_sign with z, 0
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zint_compare_magnitude" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compare |a| versus |b|. Returns -1 if |a| < |b|, 0 if equal,
    +1 if |a| > |b|.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    First compare used counts; if equal walk limbs high-to-low until a
    difference is found.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(max(used_a, used_b)).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET; control flow leaks magnitude difference position.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let ua be proc zint_get_used with a
    Let ub be proc zint_get_used with b
    If ua is less than ub:
        Return 0 minus 1
    End If
    If ua is greater than ub:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let i be ua
    While i is greater than 0:
        Set i to i minus 1
        Let la be proc zint_get_limb with a, i
        Let lb be proc zint_get_limb with b, i
        If la is less than lb:
            Return 0 minus 1
        End If
        If la is greater than lb:
            Return 1
        End If
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "zint_compare" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Signed comparison. Returns -1 if a < b, 0 if a == b, +1 if a > b.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Handle sign cases:
      - a < 0 and b >= 0: a < b.
      - a >= 0 and b < 0: a > b.
      - both nonnegative: compare magnitudes directly.
      - both negative: reverse the magnitude comparison.
    A negative zero is impossible because zero is canonicalised to
    sign = 0 by zint_normalize.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(max(used_a, used_b)).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let sa be proc zint_get_sign with a
    Let sb be proc zint_get_sign with b
    If sa is equal to 1:
        If sb is equal to 0:
            Return 0 minus 1
        End If
        Let mag be proc zint_compare_magnitude with a, b
        Return 0 minus mag
    End If
    If sb is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return proc zint_compare_magnitude with a, b
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
ADD / SUB
==============================================================================

Internally we implement unsigned magnitude addition / subtraction and
let zint_add / zint_sub dispatch by sign. The magnitude routines assume
the caller has already ensured the destination has enough capacity.
:End Note

Process called "zint_add_mag_into" takes out_z as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compute |out| = |a| + |b| (magnitude only) and store the result
    into out_z. Sets out.used to the new length and leaves out.sign
    untouched.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Walk limbs lowest-first with a single-bit carry. Use the spare
    32nd bit of int32 as the carry workspace; mask each result back
    to 31 bits before storing.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(max(used_a, used_b)).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let ua be proc zint_get_used with a
    Let ub be proc zint_get_used with b
    Let max_u be ua
    If ub is greater than max_u:
        Set max_u to ub
    End If
    Let cap be proc zint_get_capacity with out_z
    If (max_u plus 1) is greater than cap:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mask be proc zint_limb_mask
    Let bits be proc zint_limb_bits
    Let carry be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than max_u:
        Let la be proc zint_get_limb with a, i
        Let lb be proc zint_get_limb with b, i
        Let sum be la plus lb
        Set sum to sum plus carry
        Let limb be sum bitwise_and mask
        Set carry to sum shifted right by bits
        proc zint_set_limb with out_z, i, limb
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let new_used be max_u
    If carry is not equal to 0:
        proc zint_set_limb with out_z, max_u, carry
        Set new_used to max_u plus 1
    End If
    Note: Zero any leftover trailing limbs within capacity so the
    Note: destination remains canonical even when reused across many
    Note: operations.
    Let j be new_used
    While j is less than cap:
        proc zint_set_limb with out_z, j, 0
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While
    proc zint_set_used with out_z, new_used
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zint_sub_mag_into" takes out_z as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compute |out| = |a| - |b| (magnitude only) where the caller has
    guaranteed |a| >= |b|. Stores into out_z and updates out.used.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Walk limbs lowest-first with a single-bit borrow. The result limb
    is (la - lb - borrow) modulo 2^31; the borrow is 1 iff the bare
    subtraction yields a negative intermediate.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(used_a).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET. Caller-precondition violations (|a| < |b|) corrupt the
    output; zint_sub dispatcher always feeds the correct order.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let ua be proc zint_get_used with a
    Let mask be proc zint_limb_mask
    Let bits be proc zint_limb_bits
    Let radix be proc zint_limb_radix
    Let cap be proc zint_get_capacity with out_z
    If ua is greater than cap:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let borrow be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than ua:
        Let la be proc zint_get_limb with a, i
        Let lb be proc zint_get_limb with b, i
        Let diff be la minus lb
        Set diff to diff minus borrow
        If diff is less than 0:
            Set diff to diff plus radix
            Set borrow to 1
        Otherwise:
            Set borrow to 0
        End If
        Let limb_val be diff bitwise_and mask
        proc zint_set_limb with out_z, i, limb_val
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Note: borrow must be zero here because the caller guaranteed
    Note: |a| >= |b|. Zero out trailing limbs within capacity.
    Let j be ua
    While j is less than cap:
        proc zint_set_limb with out_z, j, 0
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While
    Note: Commit used to the upper bound so the trim loop can read the
    Note: limbs we just wrote via zint_get_limb (which guards on used).
    proc zint_set_used with out_z, ua
    Note: New used count: drop trailing zero limbs of the result.
    Let new_used be ua
    Let scanning be 1
    While scanning is equal to 1:
        If new_used is equal to 0:
            Set scanning to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let top be proc zint_get_limb with out_z, new_used minus 1
            If top is equal to 0:
                Set new_used to new_used minus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set scanning to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    proc zint_set_used with out_z, new_used
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zint_add" takes out_z as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Signed addition: out = a + b. out may alias a or b (we read sign /
    used from the operands first then overwrite limbs in-place safely
    because addition writes limbs in increasing index order with carry
    forward).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Same-sign:  add magnitudes, keep that sign.
    Diff-sign:  subtract smaller magnitude from larger; sign is the
                sign of the larger operand. If magnitudes are equal,
                result is zero with sign 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(max(used_a, used_b)).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let sa be proc zint_get_sign with a
    Let sb be proc zint_get_sign with b
    If sa is equal to sb:
        proc zint_add_mag_into with out_z, a, b
        proc zint_set_sign with out_z, sa
        proc zint_normalize with out_z
        Return 1
    End If
    Let cmp be proc zint_compare_magnitude with a, b
    If cmp is equal to 0:
        proc zint_set_zero with out_z
        Return 1
    End If
    If cmp is greater than 0:
        proc zint_sub_mag_into with out_z, a, b
        proc zint_set_sign with out_z, sa
    Otherwise:
        proc zint_sub_mag_into with out_z, b, a
        proc zint_set_sign with out_z, sb
    End If
    proc zint_normalize with out_z
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zint_sub" takes out_z as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Signed subtraction: out = a - b.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Diff-sign: add magnitudes, keep sign of a.
    Same-sign: subtract magnitudes; sign is sign(a) if |a| > |b|,
               opposite-of-sign(a) if |a| < |b|, zero if equal.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(max(used_a, used_b)).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let sa be proc zint_get_sign with a
    Let sb be proc zint_get_sign with b
    If sa is not equal to sb:
        proc zint_add_mag_into with out_z, a, b
        proc zint_set_sign with out_z, sa
        proc zint_normalize with out_z
        Return 1
    End If
    Let cmp be proc zint_compare_magnitude with a, b
    If cmp is equal to 0:
        proc zint_set_zero with out_z
        Return 1
    End If
    If cmp is greater than 0:
        proc zint_sub_mag_into with out_z, a, b
        proc zint_set_sign with out_z, sa
    Otherwise:
        proc zint_sub_mag_into with out_z, b, a
        Let opp_sign be sa bitwise_xor 1
        proc zint_set_sign with out_z, opp_sign
    End If
    proc zint_normalize with out_z
    Return 1
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
MULTIPLY
==============================================================================
Schoolbook for small inputs, Karatsuba for large ones. The threshold
was picked so that the asymptotic crossover lines up with the typical
NTRUSolve descent: at depth 0..5 the operands are small (under 16
limbs) and schoolbook wins; at depth 6+ Karatsuba dominates.
:End Note

Process called "zint_karatsuba_threshold" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Return the limb count above which Karatsuba multiplication is used
    in preference to schoolbook.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Constant 32 (empirically near the crossover for 31-bit limbs).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return 32
End Process

Process called "zint_mul_schoolbook" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Multiply zints a and b via O(used_a * used_b) schoolbook. Returns
    a freshly allocated zint.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    For each (i, j) accumulate la[i] * lb[j] into limb (i + j) of the
    output, propagating carry through subsequent limbs. The product
    of two 31-bit limbs fits in 62 bits, leaving 2 bits of carry slack
    per partial product; we accumulate into an int64 accumulator and
    flush low 31 bits + carry every inner iteration.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(ua * ub). For ua = ub = 16 this is 256 multiplies.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET. Multiplications run unconditionally; the only data-dep
    branch is the trailing-zero trim at the end.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let ua be proc zint_get_used with a
    Let ub be proc zint_get_used with b
    If ua is equal to 0:
        Return proc zint_from_int with arena, 0
    End If
    If ub is equal to 0:
        Return proc zint_from_int with arena, 0
    End If
    Let out_cap be ua plus ub plus 1
    Let out_z be proc zint_create with arena, out_cap
    If out_z is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mask be proc zint_limb_mask
    Let bits be proc zint_limb_bits
    Note: Pre-commit used = out_cap so the accumulator and trim loops
    Note: can read intermediate limbs via zint_get_limb (which guards
    Note: on used). The final used is reset below after the trim pass.
    proc zint_set_used with out_z, out_cap
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than ua:
        Let la be proc zint_get_limb with a, i
        Let carry be 0
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than ub:
            Let lb be proc zint_get_limb with b, j
            Let dst_idx be i plus j
            Let cur be proc zint_get_limb with out_z, dst_idx
            Let prod be la multiplied by lb
            Let total be prod plus cur
            Set total to total plus carry
            Let new_limb be total bitwise_and mask
            Set carry to total shifted right by bits
            proc zint_set_limb with out_z, dst_idx, new_limb
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        Note: Propagate any leftover carry from this row.
        Let k be i plus ub
        While carry is not equal to 0:
            Let cur2 be proc zint_get_limb with out_z, k
            Let total2 be cur2 plus carry
            Let masked_v be total2 bitwise_and mask
            proc zint_set_limb with out_z, k, masked_v
            Set carry to total2 shifted right by bits
            Set k to k plus 1
        End While
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Note: Compute final used count by trimming trailing zeros.
    Let used be out_cap
    Let scanning be 1
    While scanning is equal to 1:
        If used is equal to 0:
            Set scanning to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let top be proc zint_get_limb with out_z, used minus 1
            If top is equal to 0:
                Set used to used minus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set scanning to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    proc zint_set_used with out_z, used
    Let sa be proc zint_get_sign with a
    Let sb be proc zint_get_sign with b
    Let prod_sign be sa bitwise_xor sb
    proc zint_set_sign with out_z, prod_sign
    proc zint_normalize with out_z
    Return out_z
End Process

Process called "zint_split_low_high" takes arena as Integer, src as Integer, half_limbs as Integer, low_out_ptr as Integer, high_out_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Split src into low half (first half_limbs limbs) and high half
    (remaining limbs). Used by Karatsuba.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Allocate two zints; low gets limbs [0, half), high gets limbs
    [half, used). Both are nonnegative.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(used).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let used be proc zint_get_used with src
    Let low_used be half_limbs
    If low_used is greater than used:
        Set low_used to used
    End If
    Let high_used be 0
    If used is greater than half_limbs:
        Set high_used to used minus half_limbs
    End If
    Let low_cap be low_used
    If low_cap is less than 1:
        Set low_cap to 1
    End If
    Let high_cap be high_used
    If high_cap is less than 1:
        Set high_cap to 1
    End If
    Let low_z be proc zint_create with arena, low_cap
    Let high_z be proc zint_create with arena, high_cap
    If high_z is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than low_used:
        Let v be proc zint_get_limb with src, i
        proc zint_set_limb with low_z, i, v
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc zint_set_used with low_z, low_used
    Let j be 0
    While j is less than high_used:
        Let v2 be proc zint_get_limb with src, half_limbs plus j
        proc zint_set_limb with high_z, j, v2
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While
    proc zint_set_used with high_z, high_used
    proc zint_normalize with low_z
    proc zint_normalize with high_z
    Memory.memory_set_int64(low_out_ptr, 0, low_z)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(high_out_ptr, 0, high_z)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zint_shift_limbs_left" takes arena as Integer, src as Integer, limbs as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Multiply src by 2^(31*limbs) by prepending `limbs` zero limbs.
    Returns a freshly allocated zint.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Allocate src.used + limbs limbs, leave low `limbs` limbs as zero,
    copy src into the top.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(src.used + limbs).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let used be proc zint_get_used with src
    If used is equal to 0:
        Return proc zint_from_int with arena, 0
    End If
    Let new_used be used plus limbs
    Let dst be proc zint_create with arena, new_used
    If dst is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than used:
        Let v be proc zint_get_limb with src, i
        proc zint_set_limb with dst, i plus limbs, v
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc zint_set_used with dst, new_used
    Let src_sign be proc zint_get_sign with src
    proc zint_set_sign with dst, src_sign
    proc zint_normalize with dst
    Return dst
End Process

Process called "zint_mul_karatsuba" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Karatsuba multiplication: 3 multiplies of half-size operands plus
    O(n) adds. Recurses down to schoolbook when both operands fit
    within the schoolbook threshold.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Let n = max(used_a, used_b) / 2 rounded up. Split each operand
    into (low, high) where high gets the top limbs. Then

        a*b = high_a*high_b * B^(2n) + low_a*low_b
              + ((high_a + low_a) * (high_b + low_b)
                 - high_a*high_b - low_a*low_b) * B^n

    Sign handling is collapsed into a single XOR after the unsigned
    magnitude result is computed.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(n^1.585). Crosses over schoolbook at ~32 limbs in our setting.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let ua be proc zint_get_used with a
    Let ub be proc zint_get_used with b
    Let threshold be proc zint_karatsuba_threshold
    If ua is less than threshold:
        Return proc zint_mul_schoolbook with arena, a, b
    End If
    If ub is less than threshold:
        Return proc zint_mul_schoolbook with arena, a, b
    End If
    Let max_used be ua
    If ub is greater than max_used:
        Set max_used to ub
    End If
    Let half_limbs be (max_used plus 1) shifted right by 1

    Let low_a_ptr be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 8)
    Let high_a_ptr be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 8)
    Let low_b_ptr be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 8)
    Let high_b_ptr be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 8)
    proc zint_split_low_high with arena, a, half_limbs, low_a_ptr, high_a_ptr
    proc zint_split_low_high with arena, b, half_limbs, low_b_ptr, high_b_ptr
    Let low_a be Memory.memory_get_int64(low_a_ptr, 0)
    Let high_a be Memory.memory_get_int64(high_a_ptr, 0)
    Let low_b be Memory.memory_get_int64(low_b_ptr, 0)
    Let high_b be Memory.memory_get_int64(high_b_ptr, 0)

    Note: Use unsigned magnitudes for the recursive multiplies; the
    Note: sign of the final result is the XOR of the input signs.
    proc zint_abs with low_a
    proc zint_abs with high_a
    proc zint_abs with low_b
    proc zint_abs with high_b

    Let z0 be proc zint_mul_karatsuba with arena, low_a, low_b
    Let z2 be proc zint_mul_karatsuba with arena, high_a, high_b

    Let sum_a_cap be (proc zint_get_used with low_a) plus (proc zint_get_used with high_a) plus 2
    Let sum_b_cap be (proc zint_get_used with low_b) plus (proc zint_get_used with high_b) plus 2
    Let sum_a be proc zint_create with arena, sum_a_cap
    Let sum_b be proc zint_create with arena, sum_b_cap
    proc zint_add with sum_a, low_a, high_a
    proc zint_add with sum_b, low_b, high_b

    Let z1_full be proc zint_mul_karatsuba with arena, sum_a, sum_b
    Let z1_cap be proc zint_get_used with z1_full
    Set z1_cap to z1_cap plus 2
    Let z1 be proc zint_create with arena, z1_cap
    proc zint_sub with z1, z1_full, z0
    Let z1_tmp_cap be proc zint_get_used with z1
    Set z1_tmp_cap to z1_tmp_cap plus 2
    Let z1_tmp be proc zint_create with arena, z1_tmp_cap
    proc zint_sub with z1_tmp, z1, z2
    Set z1 to z1_tmp

    Let z1_shifted be proc zint_shift_limbs_left with arena, z1, half_limbs
    Let z2_shifted be proc zint_shift_limbs_left with arena, z2, half_limbs multiplied by 2

    Let acc_cap be (proc zint_get_used with z2_shifted) plus 2
    If (proc zint_get_used with z1_shifted) plus 2 is greater than acc_cap:
        Set acc_cap to (proc zint_get_used with z1_shifted) plus 2
    End If
    If (proc zint_get_used with z0) plus 2 is greater than acc_cap:
        Set acc_cap to (proc zint_get_used with z0) plus 2
    End If
    Let acc be proc zint_create with arena, acc_cap
    proc zint_add with acc, z0, z1_shifted
    Let acc2_cap be (proc zint_get_used with acc) plus 2
    If (proc zint_get_used with z2_shifted) plus 2 is greater than acc2_cap:
        Set acc2_cap to (proc zint_get_used with z2_shifted) plus 2
    End If
    Let acc2 be proc zint_create with arena, acc2_cap
    proc zint_add with acc2, acc, z2_shifted

    Let sa be proc zint_get_sign with a
    Let sb be proc zint_get_sign with b
    Let kar_sign be sa bitwise_xor sb
    proc zint_set_sign with acc2, kar_sign
    proc zint_normalize with acc2
    Return acc2
End Process

Process called "zint_mul" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Public multiplication entry point. Dispatches to Karatsuba for
    large operands and schoolbook for small ones.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Threshold check on max(used_a, used_b).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    See zint_mul_karatsuba and zint_mul_schoolbook.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let ua be proc zint_get_used with a
    Let ub be proc zint_get_used with b
    Let mx be ua
    If ub is greater than mx:
        Set mx to ub
    End If
    Let threshold be proc zint_karatsuba_threshold
    If mx is less than threshold:
        Return proc zint_mul_schoolbook with arena, a, b
    End If
    Return proc zint_mul_karatsuba with arena, a, b
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
SHIFTS
==============================================================================
:End Note

Process called "zint_shift_left" takes arena as Integer, src as Integer, shift_bits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compute src * 2^shift_bits. Returns a fresh zint.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Decompose shift_bits = whole_limbs * 31 + bit_offset. First shift
    by whole_limbs full limbs (free), then by bit_offset within each
    limb. The bit-shift step splits each limb into low (bit_offset bits
    pushed up) and high (carry into next limb).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(used).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let used be proc zint_get_used with src
    If used is equal to 0:
        Return proc zint_from_int with arena, 0
    End If
    If shift_bits is equal to 0:
        Return proc zint_copy with arena, src
    End If
    Let bits_per be proc zint_limb_bits
    Let mask be proc zint_limb_mask
    Let whole be shift_bits divided by bits_per
    Let frac be shift_bits minus (whole multiplied by bits_per)
    Let out_cap be used plus whole plus 2
    Let dst be proc zint_create with arena, out_cap
    If dst is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let carry be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than used:
        Let v be proc zint_get_limb with src, i
        Let shifted be (v shifted left by frac) bitwise_or carry
        Let limb_val be shifted bitwise_and mask
        Set carry to shifted shifted right by bits_per
        proc zint_set_limb with dst, i plus whole, limb_val
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let new_used be used plus whole
    If carry is not equal to 0:
        proc zint_set_limb with dst, new_used, carry
        Set new_used to new_used plus 1
    End If
    proc zint_set_used with dst, new_used
    Let src_sign be proc zint_get_sign with src
    proc zint_set_sign with dst, src_sign
    proc zint_normalize with dst
    Return dst
End Process

Process called "zint_shift_left_one_inplace" takes z as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Shift z left by 1 bit, in place.  Assumes z has at least one spare
    limb of capacity above used so that the carry-out can be absorbed
    without reallocation.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Walk limbs lowest-first: new_limb = (old_limb << 1 | carry) & mask;
    carry = old_limb >> 30 (the bit being shifted out).  After the loop,
    if carry is nonzero, append it as a new top limb and bump used.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(used).  Allocates nothing.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let used be proc zint_get_used with z
    Let cap be proc zint_get_capacity with z
    Let mask be proc zint_limb_mask
    Let bits be proc zint_limb_bits
    Let carry be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than used:
        Let v be proc zint_get_limb with z, i
        Let shifted be (v shifted left by 1) bitwise_or carry
        Let limb_val be shifted bitwise_and mask
        Set carry to (v shifted right by (bits minus 1)) bitwise_and 1
        proc zint_set_limb with z, i, limb_val
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    If carry is not equal to 0:
        If used is less than cap:
            proc zint_set_limb with z, used, 1
            proc zint_set_used with z, used plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zint_shift_right" takes arena as Integer, src as Integer, shift_bits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compute floor(|src| / 2^shift_bits) for nonnegative semantics on
    magnitude, then restore the original sign. (Caller can layer
    round-toward-zero or floor-division on top via zint_add/sub.)
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Decompose shift_bits = whole * 31 + frac. Drop whole low limbs,
    then within each surviving limb shift right by frac, OR with the
    low bits of the next limb shifted up by (31 - frac).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(used).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let used be proc zint_get_used with src
    If used is equal to 0:
        Return proc zint_from_int with arena, 0
    End If
    If shift_bits is equal to 0:
        Return proc zint_copy with arena, src
    End If
    Let bits_per be proc zint_limb_bits
    Let mask be proc zint_limb_mask
    Let whole be shift_bits divided by bits_per
    Let frac be shift_bits minus (whole multiplied by bits_per)
    If whole is greater than or equal to used:
        Return proc zint_from_int with arena, 0
    End If
    Let new_used be used minus whole
    Let dst be proc zint_create with arena, new_used plus 1
    If dst is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let inv_frac be bits_per minus frac
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than new_used:
        Let src_low be proc zint_get_limb with src, i plus whole
        Let src_high be 0
        If (i plus whole plus 1) is less than used:
            Set src_high to proc zint_get_limb with src, i plus whole plus 1
        End If
        Let part_low be src_low shifted right by frac
        Let part_high be 0
        If frac is not equal to 0:
            Set part_high to (src_high shifted left by inv_frac) bitwise_and mask
        End If
        Let limb_val be (part_low bitwise_or part_high) bitwise_and mask
        proc zint_set_limb with dst, i, limb_val
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc zint_set_used with dst, new_used
    Let src_sign be proc zint_get_sign with src
    proc zint_set_sign with dst, src_sign
    proc zint_normalize with dst
    Return dst
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
DIVISION / MODULO
==============================================================================

Long division using the textbook subtract-and-shift algorithm. The
quotient and remainder are computed simultaneously. Sign rules:
truncated division (round toward zero), with the remainder taking the
sign of the dividend.
:End Note

Process called "zint_divmod" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer, quot_out_ptr as Integer, rem_out_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compute (quot, rem) with a = quot*b + rem, |rem| < |b|, sign(rem)
    = sign(a). Returns 1 on success, 0 if b is zero.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Bit-serial long division:
      r = 0
      for bit i from msb(a) down to 0:
        r = (r << 1) | bit_i(|a|)
        if r >= |b|:
          r -= |b|
          set bit_i(quot) = 1
    Sign post-pass: quot.sign = sa XOR sb (if any nonzero); rem.sign = sa.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(bits(a) * limbs(b)). For Falcon NTRUSolve depth-9 (~2560 bits)
    this is acceptable; the descent's hot inner loop is multiplication,
    not division.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET. Bit-serial control flow leaks the bit length of the
    operands, which is a Falcon-permitted leakage path.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let bits_b be proc zint_bit_length with b
    If bits_b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sa be proc zint_get_sign with a
    Let sb be proc zint_get_sign with b
    Let bits_a be proc zint_bit_length with a
    Let bits_per be proc zint_limb_bits
    Let quot_limbs be (bits_a divided by bits_per) plus 2
    Let rem_limbs be (bits_b divided by bits_per) plus 2
    Let quot be proc zint_create with arena, quot_limbs
    Let rem be proc zint_create with arena, rem_limbs
    proc zint_set_used with quot, 0
    proc zint_set_used with rem, 0

    Note: Take unsigned magnitudes (cheap: just clear sign).
    Let abs_a be proc zint_copy with arena, a
    Let abs_b be proc zint_copy with arena, b
    proc zint_abs with abs_a
    proc zint_abs with abs_b

    Note: Initialise quot limbs to zero so we can OR bits in.
    Let qi be 0
    While qi is less than quot_limbs:
        proc zint_set_limb with quot, qi, 0
        Set qi to qi plus 1
    End While
    proc zint_set_used with quot, quot_limbs

    Note: Bit-serial loop high bit to low bit of abs_a, all in place
    Note: against the pre-allocated rem buffer.  No per-iteration zint
    Note: allocations means the inner cost is purely arithmetic.
    Let bit_i be bits_a minus 1
    While bit_i is greater than or equal to 0:
        Note: r <<= 1 (in place).
        proc zint_shift_left_one_inplace with rem

        Note: bit_a = (abs_a >> bit_i) & 1 by inspecting limb / position.
        Let limb_idx be bit_i divided by bits_per
        Let bit_idx be bit_i minus (limb_idx multiplied by bits_per)
        Let la be proc zint_get_limb with abs_a, limb_idx
        Let bit_a be (la shifted right by bit_idx) bitwise_and 1

        Note: OR bit_a into rem's lowest limb.
        If bit_a is equal to 1:
            Let rem_used be proc zint_get_used with rem
            If rem_used is equal to 0:
                proc zint_set_limb with rem, 0, 1
                proc zint_set_used with rem, 1
            Otherwise:
                Let r0 be proc zint_get_limb with rem, 0
                Let new_r0 be r0 bitwise_or 1
                proc zint_set_limb with rem, 0, new_r0
            End If
        End If

        Note: if rem >= |b|, subtract abs_b from rem in place and set the
        Note: quotient bit.
        Let cmp be proc zint_compare_magnitude with rem, abs_b
        If cmp is greater than or equal to 0:
            proc zint_sub_mag_into with rem, rem, abs_b

            Note: Set quotient bit bit_i = (limb_idx, bit_idx within limb).
            Let q_limb be proc zint_get_limb with quot, limb_idx
            Let bit_mask be 1 shifted left by bit_idx
            Let new_q be q_limb bitwise_or bit_mask
            proc zint_set_limb with quot, limb_idx, new_q
        End If

        Set bit_i to bit_i minus 1
    End While

    proc zint_normalize with quot
    proc zint_normalize with rem
    Let q_sign be sa bitwise_xor sb
    If (proc zint_get_used with quot) is equal to 0:
        Set q_sign to 0
    End If
    proc zint_set_sign with quot, q_sign
    If (proc zint_get_used with rem) is equal to 0:
        proc zint_set_sign with rem, 0
    Otherwise:
        proc zint_set_sign with rem, sa
    End If

    Memory.memory_set_int64(quot_out_ptr, 0, quot)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(rem_out_ptr, 0, rem)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "zint_div" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Return quotient of a/b. Returns 0 (pointer) on division by zero.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Calls zint_divmod and discards remainder.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    See zint_divmod.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q_ptr be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 8)
    Let r_ptr be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 8)
    Let rc be proc zint_divmod with arena, a, b, q_ptr, r_ptr
    If rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_int64(q_ptr, 0)
End Process

Process called "zint_mod" takes arena as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Return remainder of a/b with sign of a.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Calls zint_divmod and discards quotient.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    See zint_divmod.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    SECRET.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q_ptr be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 8)
    Let r_ptr be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 8)
    Let rc be proc zint_divmod with arena, a, b, q_ptr, r_ptr
    If rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_int64(r_ptr, 0)
End Process

Note:
==============================================================================
END falcon_zint
==============================================================================
:End Note
